@node 1 "What the fuck..."

SnatchDIZ  is  another  FILE_ID.DIZ extractor for the Shell or for use with
any bbs-system.  Features:

 - LHA-, LZX-, ZIP-, DMS-, EXE-, GIF-, TXT-Support
 - SnatchDIZ is smaller than 3 KB and faaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaast!
 - great code: SnatchDIZ does not produce HITS like WhaDIZ, SpeeDIZ etc.
 - good error handling: No problems with empty files or something

-=> Use SnatchDIZ instead of all the other crap floating around!
@endnode
@node 2 "It's easy..."

Usage: SnatchDIZ FILE/A,S=SUPPRESS/S,K=KEEPDIZ/S
==============================================

For example:  "SnatchDIZ dh0:down/PPLAY41.LZX S K" will give you

--------------------------------------
Power Player 4.1 Final Omega Version
* Latest Update! *
--------------------------------------

This extracts and shows the FILE_ID, suppresses the About text and does NOT
delete  the  file  t:file_id.diz (which is temporarily created) so that you
may  use  it  in any way.  The file t:file_id.diz is only created for dms-,
lha-, lzx- and zip-files.


WARNINGS: - SnatchDIZ is cli-only so don't start from Workbench!
          - SnatchDIZ was NOT TESTED AT ALL with GIFs!
@endnode
@node 3 "You got this crap..."

You need:

 - an AMIGA w/Kick 2.04+ (as always).
 - the lha-, lzx-, GIFdesc- and UNzip-executable placed in your path.
   A working UNzip and GIFdesc is included in the SnatchDIZ-archive.

That's it.
@endnode
